We’re all struggling to get comfortable in this heatwave and, judging by these photos, cats are not emerging unscathed. People have shared snaps of their moggies looking as if they’ve literally melted, and pulling some wildly contorted poses in a bid to cool off. Honestly, we relate. But, before we get to the silly pics, a warning: cats can suffer dangerous consequences of overheating and too much sun exposure – just like humans can. It’s all well and good having a giggle at cute photos, but make sure you also know how to keep your cat safe in these extreme temperatures and keep an eye out for the symptoms of heatstroke. Flat-faced breeds, such as Persian cats, also have an increased risk of getting heatstroke. Their short muzzles can make breathing difficult, and therefore it’s even harder for them to keep cool. Older and heavier pets are also more likely to struggle. OK, now that we’ve established the safety ground rules, here’s your reward… Do you have a story to share? Get in touch by emailing MetroLifestyleTeam@Metro.co.uk MORE : Can you give 17-year-old cats Thelma and Louise a retirement home? MORE : Nearly half of dog owners don’t know their pets need to wear sunscreen in hot weather MORE : Our sweat-proof makeup edit – perfect for a heatwave